and techniques</td>
<td style="text-align:left;border-left:2px solid #fdfdfd;width:100%;padding:0px;;;" class="navbox-list navbox-odd">
<div style="padding:0em 0.25em"><a href="/wiki/Deep_time" title="Deep time">Deep time</a><span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span> <a href="/wiki/Geological_history_of_Earth" title="Geological history of Earth">Geological history</a><span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span> <u>Geological time units</u>: <a href="/wiki/Eon_(geology)" title="Eon (geology)" class="mw-redirect">Eons</a><span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span> <a href="/wiki/Era_(geology)" title="Era (geology)" class="mw-redirect">Eras</a><span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span> <a href="/wiki/Period_(geology)" title="Period (geology)" class="mw-redirect">Periods</a> •&#160;<a href="/wiki/Epoch_(geology)" title="Epoch (geology)" class="mw-redirect">Epoch</a> •&#160;<a href="/wiki/Age_(geology)" title="Age (geology)" class="mw-redirect">Age</a> <u>Dating Standards</u>: <a href="/wiki/GSSA" title="GSSA" class="mw-redirect">GSSA</a> •&#160;<a href="/wiki/GSSP" title="GSSP" class="mw-redirect">GSSP</a><br />
<a href="/wiki/Chronostratigraphy" title="Chronostratigraphy">Chronostratigraphy</a><span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span> <a href="/wiki/Geochronology" title="Geochronology">Geochronology</a><span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span> <a href="/wiki/Isotope_geochemistry" title="Isotope geochemistry">Isotope geochemistry</a><span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span> <a href="/wiki/Law_of_superposition" title="Law of superposition">Law of superposition</a><span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span> <a href="/wiki/Optical_dating" title="Optical dating">Optical dating</a><span style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;·</span> <a href="/wiki/Samarium-neodymium_dating" title="Samarium-neodymium dating">Samarium-neodymium dating</a></div>
</td>
